- Use `@sentry/nextjs` for error tracking.
- No `console.log/warn/debug` in production. Gate debug logs behind `NODE_ENV === "development"`.
- Replace `console.error` with `Sentry.captureException(error, { tags, extra })`.
- User messaging: never show raw errors; use `react-hot-toast` with generic text; optional short error code.
- Tagging/context: tags `{ area, operation, module, severity }`; extra non-PII only; include `tenantId`/`userId` when available.
- Exceptions: webhook signature verification failures (minimal `console.error` + Sentry); development-only code paths.
- Biome enforcement: `"style": { "noConsole": "error" }` in `biome.json`; use ignores only for exceptions above.

